Turkey helicopter crash: 12 dead as police chopper goes down in Tunceli
HORROR: 12 people have been killed in the crash
The helicopter was carrying a judge, seven police officers, one sergeant and three crew members, the governor’s office in Tunceli, Turkey, said in a statement. 
The S-70 Blackhawk helicopter crash may have been caused by poor weather conditions in the mountainous region, they added.
It went down just 10 minutes after taking off from the town of Pulumur.